body.p:
Line wrapping doesn't apply on inline elements, some lines of code may bleed out of the
      page due to that. To allow wrapping, the property should be set on the parent block with the
      following rule in your customization
        CSS:*:has(*[class ~= 'pr-d/codeph']) {
  overflow-wrap: break-word;
}


It is possible to use hyphens: auto instead of overflow-wrap:
              break-word.

It is possible to use the same rule for software domain elements, like
              filepath or cmdname.
